钟南山团队最新研究论文：患者潜伏期最长24天 初次就诊相当部分患者未发热和CT异常。
The latest study by Zhong Nan Shan team: Patients with latency of up to 24 days for the first visit quite a number of patients without fever and CT abnormalities.
黄一帆2020-02-10 17:36。
Yifan Huang 2020-02-10 17: 36.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察网 记者 黄一帆2月9日，由国家卫健委高级别专家组组长、中国工程院院士钟南山领衔的“中国2019年新型冠状病毒感染的临床特征”回顾性研究，在预印本网站medRxiv上发表。
A retrospective study on "Clinical Features of the New Coronavirus Infection in 2019 in China" led by Zhong Nan-shan, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and head of the high-level group of experts, was published on the pre-printed website medRxiv.
（注：medRxiv的论文均未经同行评审）。
(Note: None of medRxiv's papers were peer-reviewed).
。
.
截至1月29日，该研究对全国1099例患者进行了回顾性研究。
As of Jan. 29, the study included a retrospective study of 1,099 patients nationwide.
值得注意的是，据研究样本统计，患者潜伏期中位数为3天，最长可达24天。
It is worth noting that the median incubation period for patients was 3 days and up to 24 days, according to the study sample.
初次就诊时，相当一部分患者没有发烧和放射学异常，而腹泻并不常见。
At the time of the initial visit, a significant proportion of patients had no fever and radiologic abnormalities, and diarrhoea was uncommon.
。
.
2月10日，该论文研究团队成员之一的关伟杰在媒体采访时表示，目前网上流传的文章并非论文原文，而是研究的预印稿，供专家评议使用。
In a media interview on Feb. 10, Guan Weijie, a member of the paper's research team, said the articles circulated online were not the original papers but pre-printed versions of the research for expert review.
目前论文还在投稿阶段，发布前需要全球同行评议。
The paper is still in the manuscript stage and will require global peer review prior to release.
针对文中披露的潜伏期最长为24天，关伟杰表示，仍是个例。
The maximum incubation period disclosed in the article was 24 days, Mr Kwan said, still an exception.
。
.
中位潜伏期3天 出现潜伏期24天患者。
The median incubation period was 3 days with 24 days incubation period.
据了解，该论文为钟南山等人对来自31个省/市辖市、552家医院的1099例（截至1月29日）新冠肺炎确诊患者的临床特征进行了回顾性研究。
It is understood that a retrospective study was conducted by Zhong Nan Shan et al., on the clinical characteristics of 1,099 cases (as of 29 January) of newly diagnosed cases of crown pneumonia from 552 hospitals in 31 provincial / municipal municipalities.
。
.
该论文由钟南山携手来自全国抗疫一线的37位作者共同完成。
The paper was jointly completed by 37 authors from the first line of the national epidemic in Zhong Nan Shan.
作者单位包括广州市呼吸卫生研究所、武汉市金银潭医院。
Authors include Guangzhou Respiratory Hygiene Institute and Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital.
。
.
在这1099例患者中，2.09％为医护人员。
Of the 1,099 patients, 2.09 per cent were medical staff.
有野生动物接触史的患者仅为1.18％，而四分之三以上的人是武汉当地居民，或者与武汉人接触过。
Only 1.18 percent of the patients had any contact with wild animals, while more than three-quarters were local residents of Wuhan or had contact with Wuhan people.
。
.
值得注意的是，据研究样本统计，中位潜伏期为3天，最长达24天。
It is worth noting that the median incubation period is 3 days and up to 24 days, according to the study sample.
钟南山团队指出，中位潜伏期短于最近425例患者的报道中指出的5.2天这一数字（3.0天比5.2天）。
The Zhong Nan Shan team noted that the median incubation period was shorter than the 5.2 days reported in the most recent 425 cases (3.0 days compared to 5.2 days).
。
.
此外，该研究指出，不能排除“超级传播者”的出现。
Moreover, the study points out that the emergence of "super-disseminators" cannot be ruled out.
钟南山团队指出，该研究为人与人之间的传播提供了进一步的证据。
The Zhong Nan Shan team points out that the study provides further evidence of human-to-human transmission.
。
.
除了飞沫传播和直接接触两种途径，研究人员还在一些患者的粪便样本，以及胃肠道、唾液或尿液、食道侵蚀出血部位中检测到新冠病毒，因此钟南山团队建议，卫生保护应考虑到通过胃肠道分泌物的传播。
In addition to droplet transmission and direct contact, the researchers detected new canopy viruses in faecal samples from some patients, as well as in gastrointestinal, saliva or urine, and esophageal erosion haemorrhage, and the Zhong Nan Shan team recommended that health protection should take into account transmission through gastrointestinal secretions.
。
.
初诊时发烧症状比例低于SARS。
Fever rate at first visit was lower than that of SARS.
据研究样本统计，最常见的症状是发烧（87.9％）和咳嗽（67.7％），而腹泻（3.7％）和呕吐（5.0％）很少见。
According to the study sample, the most common symptoms were fever (87.9 per cent) and cough (67.7 per cent), while diarrhoea (3.7 per cent) and vomiting (5.0 per cent) were rare.
25.2％的患者患有至少一种基础疾病（即高血压，慢性阻塞性肺疾病）。
25.2% of patients suffer from at least one basic disease (i.e. hypertension, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease).
。
.
此外，据研究样本统计，入院时接受CT检查的840名患者中，有76.4％表现为肺炎。
In addition, according to study samples, 76.4 per cent of the 840 patients admitted to the hospital on CT showed pneumonia.
其最常见的模式是毛玻璃样混浊（50.0％）和双侧斑片状阴影（46.0％）。
The most common patterns were plexiglass-like opacity (50.0 per cent) and bilateral patch-like shadows (46.0 per cent).
。
.
尽管有这些主要表现，但通过症状加反转录酶-聚合酶链锁反应（RT-PCR）阳性结果可诊断出926例中的221例（23.87％），相比之下173例中9例（5.20％），CT没有检测出问题，但RT呈阳性的有9例。
Despite these major findings, 221 out of 926 cases (23.87 per cent) were diagnosed by symptomatic reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR), compared with 9 cases (5.20 per cent) out of 173 (5.20 per cent), but 9 cases were RT-positive.
。
.
钟南山等人在研究中主张，将重点转移到疾病发展之前的早期识别和管理患者上。
In their study, Zhong Nan-shan and others argue that the focus should shift to the early identification and management of patients before the disease progresses.
据研究样本统计，20.9％的患者在没有发展成病毒性肺炎前就已经感染。
According to the study sample, 20.9 percent of the patients were infected before they developed viral pneumonia.
。
.
“与最近的出版物一致，新型冠状病毒的临床特征模仿了SARS的临床特征。
"Consistent with recent publications, the clinical features of the new coronavirus mimic those of SARS.
发热和咳嗽是主要症状，而胃肠道症状很少见，这表明与SARS、MERS和流感相比，病毒的嗜性差异，”研究者指出。
Fever and cough are the main symptoms, while gastrointestinal symptoms are rare, suggesting differences in viral appetite compared to SARS, MERS and influenza, the researchers note.
。
.
值得注意的是，据研究样本统计，初次就诊时发烧仅占43.8％，住院后发烧的占87.9％。
It is worth noting that, according to the study sample, only 43.8 per cent of the first visits were fever and 87.9 per cent after hospitalization.
在新型冠状病毒患者中未发烧的频率远低于SARS和MERS患者。
The frequency of fever in patients with new coronavirus is much lower than that of patients with SARS and MERS.
。
.
研究者指出，如果监视病例的定义主要集中在发烧检测上，则可能会漏诊此类患者。
If surveillance cases are defined primarily in terms of fever testing, they may miss out on such patients, the researchers note.
。
.
致死率低于SARS和MERS。
Mortality rates were lower than SARS and MERS.
钟南山等人在论文中表示，和之前在《柳叶刀》上发表的两项研究相比，基于更大的样本量和在全国各地招募的病例，最新研究得出的新冠肺炎病死率明显变低（1.4%）。
Compared with two previous studies published in The Lancet, the latest study, based on a larger sample size and cases recruited across the country, showed a significantly lower death rate (1.4 per cent) from the latest study, Zhong Nan Shan and others said in their paper.
当计入广东省的试点数据时，病死率更低（0.88%）。
When pilot data from Guangdong Province were included, the fatality rate was even lower (0.88 per cent).
。
.
研究指出，早期隔离、早期诊断和早期管理可能共同导致了广东省死亡率的显著降低。
Early isolation, early diagnosis and early management may have contributed to a significant reduction in mortality in Guangdong province, the study said.
此外，由于中央管理（即武汉金银潭医院）而导致卫生人力的缺乏可能导致死亡率上升。
In addition, the lack of health manpower due to central management (i.e. Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital) may lead to an increase in mortality.
。
.
钟南山团队指出，新型冠状肺炎病死率低于SARS和MERS。
Zhong Nan Shan team pointed out that the mortality rate of new coronary pneumonia is lower than SARS and MERS.
。
.
在住院期间，新冠肺炎患者最常见的并发症是肺炎（79.1%），其次是急性呼吸系统疾病（3.37%）和休克（1.00%）。
During hospitalization, pneumonia (79.1 per cent) was the most common complication, followed by acute respiratory disease (3.37 per cent) and shock (1.00 per cent).
。
.
